Colombian Stock Movers: Almacenes Exito, Coltejer, Grupo Nutresa

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-09-19T15:48:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/colombian-stock-movers-almacenes-exito-coltejer-grupo-nutresa.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:14 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 1.1 percent to 13,731.72 while the
Colcap Index fell 1.2 percent to 1,664.85.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  , Colombia’s biggest publicly
traded retailer, fell 0.6 percent to 23,700 pesos. The Medellin-
based company is offering 114.27 million shares at 21,900 pesos
each in a sale that will end Sept. 23.  Coltejer SA (COLTEJ)  , a Colombian clothing maker and
exporter, rose 1 percent to 1.02 peso. Senate Majority Leader
 Harry Reid  said Sept. 16 that lawmakers will start work this
week on actions that may clear the way for President Barack Obama to send Congress three stalled free-trade agreements.  Grupo Nutresa SA (NUTRESA CB), Colombia’s biggest food
producer, fell 1.1 percent to 22,440 pesos.  Colombia, the second-largest producer of Arabica coffee,
forecasts above-average rainfall during the rest of this month
in areas including coffee-growing regions in the Andes
mountains, according to an e-mail statement Sept. 16 from the
Institute of Hydrology, Meteorology and Environmental Studies.
Above-average rain will likely continue in October and November,
according to the statement.  Colombia ’s National Federation of Coffee Growers said in a
Sept. 15 statement that coffee exports fell to their lowest
level since 1988 in August after storms that damaged flowering
reduced production.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
